	activity_end = system.date.format(system.date.addDays(currentDate, 1), 'yyyy-MM-dd hh:mm:ss')

	return where

messageHandlers.script:
### Refresh data
	system.perspective.print("Refresh Case Notes Dashboard")
	memActivityRange = self.view.params.activity_range
	#self.view.params.activity_range = 0

	#self.view.refreshBinding("custom.sql_data")
	#self.view.params.activity_range = memActivityRange 
#	self.view.refreshBinding("custom.sql_data")
#	self.view.refreshBinding("custom.table_data")
#	self.refreshBinding("props.data")

# implement your handler here
	import traceback
	try:
		#Send the dataset to Excel
		filename = 'Participants_CaseNotes_' + str(system.date.format(system.date.now(),"yyyyMMddHHmmss")) + '.xls'
#		dataset = self.view.custom.sql_data
#		display_columns = ['name','nickName','ssn','noteDate','hmis','CaseNoteTypeName']
#		filteredData = system.dataset.filterColumns(chartData, northSouth)
		dataset = []
		header = ["Participant Name", "Nick Name","SSN","Entered By","Note date","HMIS","Note Type","Note","Service",'Start Time','End Time']
		data = self.view.custom.sql_data
		for i in range(data.getRowCount()):
			participant_name = data.getValueAt(i,'participant_name')
			nick_name = data.getValueAt(i,'nick_name')
			ssn = data.getValueAt(i,'ssn')
			enteredBy = data.getValueAt(i,'employee_name')
			time_created = data.getValueAt(i,'time_created')
			hmis = str(data.getValueAt(i,'hmis'))
			note_type = data.getValueAt(i,'note_type')
			note = data.getValueAt(i,'note')
			service_desc = data.getValueAt(i,'service_desc')
			if data.getValueAt(i,'startTime') != None and data.getValueAt(i,'startTime') != '':
				startTime = str(system.date.format(data.getValueAt(i,'startTime'),'MM/dd/yyyy hh:mm'))
			else:
				startTime = ''
			if data.getValueAt(i,'endTime') != None and data.getValueAt(i,'endTime') != '':
				endTime = str(system.date.format(data.getValueAt(i,'endTime'),'MM/dd/yyyy hh:mm'))
			else:
				endTime = ''
			dataset.append([participant_name,nick_name,ssn,enteredBy,time_created,hmis,note_type,note,service_desc,startTime,endTime])
#		system.perspective.print(dataset)
		NewDataset = system.dataset.toDataSet(header, dataset)
#		system.perspective.print(NewDataset)
		xlFile = system.dataset.toExcel(True,NewDataset)
		system.perspective.download(filename, xlFile)
	except:   
		logger = system.util.getLogger("Participants Case Notes tableToExcel")
		msg = traceback.format_exc()
		logger.error(msg)

# implement your handler here
	self.props.selection.selectedColumn = -1
	self.props.selection.selectedRow = -1

import traceback
	try:
		#Generate the report
		project = "HMS"
		path = "ParticipantsCaseNoteDashboard"
		parameters = {'activity_range':self.view.params.activity_range,
					'notedate':self.session.custom.filters.caseNotesDashboard.NoteDate.where,
					'notetype':self.session.custom.filters.caseNotesDashboard.NoteType.where,
					'hmis':self.session.custom.filters.caseNotesDashboard.hmis.where,
					'enteredby':self.session.custom.filters.caseNotesDashboard.EnteredBy.where,
					'firstname':self.session.custom.filters.caseNotesDashboard.FirstName.where,
					'middlename':self.session.custom.filters.caseNotesDashboard.MiddleName.where,
					'lastname':self.session.custom.filters.caseNotesDashboard.LastName.where,
					'nickname':self.session.custom.filters.caseNotesDashboard.NickName.where,
					'search':self.session.custom.filters.caseNotesDashboard.Search.where,
					'program':self.view.custom.program_where,
					'service':self.session.custom.filters.caseNotesDashboard.service.where,
					'shelter':self.view.custom.shelter_string,
					'veteran':self.session.custom.filters.caseNotesDashboard.Veteran.where,
					'datefilter':self.view.custom.datefilter
					}
		pdfFile = system.report.executeReport(path,project,parameters,fileType='pdf')
		filename = 'participants_caseNote_dashboard_' + str(system.date.format(system.date.now(),"yyyyMMddHHmmss")) + '.pdf'

		system.perspective.download(filename, pdfFile)
	except:   
		logger = system.util.getLogger("Participants Case Note Dashboard tableToPDF")
		msg = traceback.format_exc()
		logger.error(msg)
